1.en: and so, although icily sardonic in conversation and convinced he would be a "superlative" writer, he never made the Ivy League.
1.cn: 于是，尽管在与人交谈时会带有不友善的讽刺，尽管确信自己会成为一个“最棒的”作家，他最终却没有迈进常春藤盟校。

2.en: With the league on the verge of missing games, Santa Stern should at least have the heart to give us five national games.
2.cn: 联盟处在停摆的边缘，斯特恩一定想要在这天为我们献上至少5场的全美比赛。

3.en: At the moment, in the league we aren't able to open up the closed defence.
3.cn: 如今，在联赛中我们不再会是保守的防守了。

0.en: Penny, there's no I In Justice League.
0.cn: 佩妮，正义联盟里没有"小我"之说。

1.en: The D-league is one of the toughest things when it comes to a basketball career. The D- league, you know, it's a showcase.
1.cn: 发展联盟是一道难关，对于篮球生涯而言，发展联盟，你懂的，它是个展示的舞台。

2.en: The warriors' management sent Jeremy down to the D-league, the NBA's version of a minor league farm system. He was faced with a harsh reality.
2.cn: 勇士的管理层把林书豪下放到发展联盟，这是NBA的小型联盟育才体系，他面对着残酷的现实。

3.en: What I told him when he went to the d-league was simple. Go kill it. Go and crush the d-league, and let's get called up. Because it's a battle, you know. It's a battle right here.
3.cn: 当他去发展联盟的时候，我对他说的话很简单，把它拿下，去把发展联盟搞定，然后等着别人给我们打电话。因为这是一场战役，这就是一场意志上的战役

4.en: Okay, now, do you really need the honorary justice league of America membership card?
4.cn: 好吧，你真的需要那张美国荣誉审判联盟的会员卡吗？

5.en: And here is my Justice League membership card. But that doesn't prove I know Batman.
5.cn: 这是我正义联盟的会员卡，但是这不能证明我认识蝙蝠侠。

6.en: Serena Van Der Woodsen wants to work for the junior league and have two children?
6.cn: 瑟琳娜 范德·伍德森想在儿童慈善联盟工作，然后生两个孩子？

7.en: I just want to make sure that we're all clear. Standard robotic fighting league rules apply.
7.cn: 我只是想确认下我们说好了，按照标准机器人格斗联盟规则。

8.en: So are you guys coming to my New Year's Eve costume party? Of course. We're coming as the Justice League of America.
8.cn: 你们几位来不来我的新年化装派对啊？当然来啊，我们要组成美国正义联盟。

9.en: Oh, please, we all know I'm the friend you call when you have no other options. If we were the Justice League, I'd be Aquaman.
9.cn: 少来了。大家都清楚你没有人了，才会来找我。如果我们是正义联盟，我就是海王子。

10.en: Major League Baseball and its fans, they're gonna be more than happy to throw you and Google Boy under the bus if you keep doing what you're doing here.
10.cn: 如果你们还是执迷不悟，职棒大联盟和球迷们会很不高兴，甚至把你和谷歌小子扔到车底去。

11.en: Okay. I don't give a shit about friendship, this situation, or the past. Major League Baseball thinks the way I think. You're not gonna win.
11.cn: 得了，我才不在乎什么友情，现在怎么样，过去怎么样，我的思路和职棒大联盟一样，你们会输得很惨。

12.en: Oh, I'm ready. I don't know if Stuart told you what you're up against tonight, but before you stands the co-captain of the East Texas Christian Youth Holy Roller Bowling League championship team. Seven to 12 year old division. Also, Penny's pretty good.
12.cn: 当然准备好了。我不知道斯图尔特有没有告诉你今晚你的对手是谁，不过站在你面前的人就是东德克萨斯州青年基督徒圣保龄同盟会冠军队的联盟队长，7到12岁参赛组。佩妮打得也不错。

13.en: So that's who you're in league with? All the fourth-years?
13.cn: 所以这就是你勾结的人吗？所有四年律师？

14.en: You know, we make a big play for the Ivy League pool for that, so…
14.cn: 这个职位我们主要面向常春藤毕业生，所以。

15.en: He was doing his job. He was out of his league. He should have waited.
15.cn: 他是尽守职责。超出了他的能力范围，他应该等待援军。

16.en: Do you have any idea how many Ivy league, Phi Beta Kappa's would kill...
16.cn: 你知道有多少常春藤毕业生和优等生想尽办法。

17.en: You know, I once scored 41 points at a league championship game. No way.
17.cn: 知道吗，我曾在联赛决赛里得了41分，不可能。

18.en: Switching it up from last year when we came as the Justice League of America.
18.cn: 阵容安排得换一下，不能和去年的重复了。

19.en: Oh, one small detail, this is an all-gay bowling league, so I told everyone you're all gay.
19.cn: 一个小细节，这是基佬保龄球联赛，所以我跟大家说你是基佬。
